.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-time_convert \- Convert between epoch, ISO 8601, RFC 3339, RFC 2822, and human-readable
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility time_convert
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Convert between epoch, ISO 8601, RFC 3339, RFC 2822, and human-readable
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.PP
Command   |   Description
\fCnow\fP   |   Current time in all formats
\fCepoch [TS]\fP   |   Convert epoch seconds (default: now)
\fCparse TIMESTAMP\fP   |   Parse any timestamp → epoch + ISO
\fCcron EXPR\fP   |   Show next N cron fire times
\fCtz [ZONE]\fP   |   Timezone info or list available zones
\fCdiff TS1 TS2\fP   |   Duration between two timestamps
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
time now
time epoch 1700000000
time epoch 1700000000 --tz UTC
time parse '2024-01-15T10:30:00Z'
time cron '*/15 * * * *' --count 5
time tz Asia/Tokyo
time diff '2024-01-01' '2024-12-31'
.EE
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Flag   |   Meaning
\fC--tz TIMEZONE\fP   |   Interpret/display in timezone
\fC--count N\fP   |   Cron: number of future fires (default 5)
\fC--json\fP   |   Machine-readable output
\fC--no-color\fP   |   Disable ANSI
.PP
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fCdate\fP (GNU or BSD) — core conversions
.IP \(bu 4
\fCpython3\fP + \fCcroniter\fP — cron parsing (\fCpip install croniter\fP)
.IP \(bu 4
\fCpython3\fP + \fCzoneinfo\fP — timezone listing (Python 3.9+)
